{"key":"processedPost-13199941","value":{"id":13199941,"first":13198976,"last":13208394,"when":1284585690,"utime":"09/16/10 12:21 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />i normally do it the same way but i use the old baking rule, of mixing my dry ingredients first then the wet.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />This is one exception to the old baking rule.&nbsp; <br /><br />The reason is that the very fine rice flour will sink to the bottom of the bowl of vermiculite, and then when you add water it will clump up and not mix well.&nbsp; By mixing the water and verm first, and then slowly adding the rice flour, you ameliorate that problem.<br />RR","title":"Re: Vermiculite to BRF to Water.., best proportion?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}